    <h2 style=3D"text-align:" center=3D"" id=3D"Rhombus-Calculator">Rhombus=
 Calculator</h2>    <p>This area of rhombus calculator can find the area of=
 rhombus through three different methods:&nbsp;</p>    <ul>  	<li>Base time=
s height method</li>  	<li>Diagonal method</li>  	<li>Trigonometry method</=
li>  </ul>    <p>You can find the perimeter of the rhombus also by entering=
 the value of length.</p>    <h2 id=3D"What-is-a-rhombus?">What is a rhombu=
s?</h2>    <p>A Rhombus is a quadrilateral with four equal sides and opposi=
te equal acute and obtuse angles. A rhombus is also a parallelogram with eq=
ual sides.&nbsp;</p>    <p>It's like a lean square whose diagonals bisect e=
ach other but need not be 90 degrees. Rhombus is also sometimes called a 'd=
iamond' or 'lozenge' shape.</p>    <p>All four sides of Rhombus are congrue=
nt. Its diagonals are <a href=3D"https://www.meracalculator.com/graphic/per=
pendicularlength.php">perpendicular</a> and bisect vertex angles.&nbsp;</p>=
    <h3>The formula of the area of the rhombus:</h3>    <p>The area of a rh=
ombus can be calculated through three different formulas. All of these form=
ulas use different values to find the area.</p>    <p><strong>Base Times He=
ight Method :</strong></p>    <p>Area of Rhombus =3D b * h</p>    <p><stron=
g>Diagonal Method</strong><strong> :</strong></p>    <p>Area of Rhombus =3D=
 =C2=BD x d<sub>1</sub> x d<sub>2</sub>&nbsp;</p>    <p><strong>Trigonometr=
y Method</strong><strong> :</strong></p>    <p>Area of Rhombus =3D a=C2=B2 =
* SinA</p>    <p><strong>Perimeter of Rhombus</strong> =3D 4(a)</p>    <p>W=
here,</p>    <p>a =3D side</p>    <p>b =3D height, d<sub>1</sub> and d<sub>=
2</sub> diagonals</p>    <h2 id=3D"How-to-calculate-the-area-of-rhombus?">H=
ow to calculate the area of rhombus?</h2>    <p><strong>Examples:</strong><=
/p>    <p><strong>Case 1:</strong> Find the area of a rhombus with the give=
n base 4 and height 5 using the Base Times Height Method.</p>    <p><strong=
>Solution:</strong> Find the area.</p>    <p>Area =3D b * h =3D 4*5 =3D <st=
rong>20</strong>.</p>    <p><strong>Case 2:</strong> Find the area of a rho=
mbus with the given diagonals 4,5 using the Diagonal Method.</p>    <p><str=
ong>Solution:</strong> Find the area.</p>    <p><strong>Area</strong> =3D =
=C2=BD * d<sub>1</sub> * d<sub>2</sub> =3D 0.5 * 4*5 =3D 20*0.5 =3D <strong=
>10</strong></p>    <p><strong>Case 3:</strong> Find the area of a rhombus =
with the given side 3 using Trigonometry Method.</p>    <p><strong>Solution=
</strong><strong>:</strong> Find the area.</p>    <p>Area =3D a=C2=B2 * Sin=
A =3D 3=C2=B2 * Sin(33) =3D 9* 1 =3D <strong>9</strong>.</p>    <p><strong>=
Case 4:</strong> Find the perimeter of a rhombus with the given side 3.</p>=
    <p><strong>Solution</strong><strong>:</strong> Find the perimeter.</p> =
   <p>Perimeter =3D 4(a) =3D 4 * 3 =3D <strong>12</strong>.</p>
